hardened_malloc aims to prevent many common memory
vulnerabilities, such as buffer overflows, double frees,
and use-after-frees. It is designed to improve security
without significant performance penalties.

can be integrated into applications in various
ways, including:

Directly: By linking applications with the hardened_malloc
          library.

With tools like firejail: To isolate and restrict the
memory access of dillo browser within a sandboxed environment.

Example:
firejail --env=LD_PRELOAD=/path/to/libhardened_malloc.so dillo
